inn1.comm: punched off the backfoot towards mid-off right off the middle of the bat
82 mph, fuller in length on middle and leg and he mistimes the drive back to the bowler
81.2 mph, the first boundary but it was chipped in the air for a while, he punches it off the backfoot just wide of cover and Elliott gives the chase, this is a quick outfield, good effort by Elliott
angles it on middle and leg, places it to midwicket
full and swinging away, he pushes it off the meat of the bat to mid-off
loses his radar and slips it wide down the leg side, the batsman tries to tickle it fine
gets a half stride forward and pushes it towards cover
hits a good length outside off and gets good carry to the keeper
kicks up a bit off a good length and he shapes to fend it off but luckily he keeps it down and angles it to third man
85.7 mph, gets a bit of late swing and the pace catches Nazir on the pads as he tries to work it to the on side
full and swinging in, he drives away from the body and gets an inside edge to midwicket
chipped in the air for a few anxious seconds but mid-off's at the edge of the circle, he mistimed that
much better, he gets his bat properly behind the line and pushes it to cover
hits a good length on middle and leg, he stands tall and punches it to mid-on
82.1 mph, brute of a delivery which kicks up and nearly shaves the gloves, close call
slightly short of a length outside off and he plays a half-hearted cut to point
short of a length but he's not in full control of the pull, the midwicket region is vacant so he's safe, Franklin cuts it off in the deep
teaser from Mills, swings in at first and deviates off the seam after pitching, Kamran is beaten
loses his direction by slipping it wide down the leg side
lands just a shade outside off and moves away, well left this time
lands outside off and swings it in, defends back to the bowler
86.5 mph, bowls it full and lands it in the length to drive, he places it square of the wicket on the off side
swings it in late and gets his direction spot on, well played by Nazir as he defends right in front of the stumps
spot on with the swing again, Nazir blocks it off the full face of the bat
holds the length back a bit and Nazir punches it straight to short cover
88 mph, good stuff from Bond as he fires it on the blockhole outside off and swings it in prodigiously, Nazir fails to squeeze it out
good timing there, lands it on a good length outside off and he merely pats it past backward point off the middle of the bat
gets forward and pushes it straight to Redmond at short cover, well fielded
Mills struggles with his line yet again and sprays it down the leg side, the ball clips his pads and rolls away
on target this time, he defends it to the off side
just a touch wide outside off, reaches out and softly taps it down to point
slower ball, he turns the face of the bat and nudges it down to short midwicket
86.2 mph, close call for Akmal, he lashes hard at a short and wide delivery outside off, the ball dips and lands in front of third man
short arm pull, Bond drops it fractionally short and Nazir has had enough of waiting, he clubs it and comfortably clears mid-on
good comeback by Bond as he beats the outside edge, Nazir goes for a booming cover drive
mixes the pace by bowling a slower ball, forces Nazir to check the punch to cover
really jams it on the blockhole outside off and Nazir squeezes it out
another slower ball, Nazir fails to read the leg cutter and the ball bounces once to the keeper
full and swinging away, he drives to mid-off
lands it on middle and leg and he clips it to the gap at square leg
lands it outside off and he deftly glides it past backward point
drops it a fraction short and he swivels and plays a short-arm pull to deep square-leg
reaches out and mistimes the drive to mid-off
spoke too soon perhaps, pitched up delivery on the off stump waiting to be smacked, Nazir does the needful by lofting him through the line miles over mid-off
85.6 mph, kicks up off a good length and Akmal does well to fend it off with soft hands
ouch! Hits him flush on the knuckles this time, kicks up again off the surface, he's in pain
better fortunes this time for Akmal as he gets his elbows high and pats it to the off side
stays nicely behind the line and defends with confidence
slower in pace this time and angling wide of the off stump, he angles it down  to third man
full and wide outside off and smacked off the front foot, should have gone for four but Broom does brilliantly at backward point to cut it off
Butler gets it wrong straightaway, he drops it short and the length is perfect for the batsman to swivel and pull it behind square
gets behind the line and taps it to the off side
fuller in length outside off and Nazir gets forward and chips it in the air slightly but places it right in the gap at the covers, nice timing there
three for the over, Butler overcompensates by pitching it too short, Nazir swivels and plays a short arm pull which nearly carries over the rope, just beats the fielder at deep square leg
stays behind the line and defends
turns the face of the bat and clips it to mid-on
lands it on a goo length on middle and leg and he works it to the on side
stays beside the line and steers it wide of point

he oversteps but New Zealand could still have got a wicket, Nazir hops to fend off a short delivery towards short midwicket and Kamran quickly gets off the blocks at the other end, he turns back and dives but luckily the throw is wide of the stumps
Free Hit Makes room but Bond fires it on the blockhole outside off and the batsman swings at thin air
brute of a delivery sends him back, Bond hits the deck hard and Nazir is forced to fend it off, it balloons off the top half of the bat and Taylor snaps the top edge at first slip
greets him with a bouncer straightaway, Malik gets his helmet out of the way
jams it on the blockhole outside off and Malik gets his bat down to squirt it out
short of a length and the batsman swivels and pulls along the turf to deep square leg
gets his bat nicely behind the line and punches it back to the bowler
gets across his stumps and clips a good length delivery down to midwicket
Butler's short length is getting a little too predictable here, Kamran reads the length early and clubs it right into the gap between two fielders at deep square leg
stays back and punches him to the off side
he gets his elbows high and punches him down to square third man, Malik wants the second but Kamran's not interested
crisp timing there, drops it short of a length outside off and just a hint of width, he gets his elbows high and punches it just wide or backward point's grasp
gets beside the line and angles it to point
stays behind the line and punches it back to the bowler
shuffles at the crease and knocks it down to midwicket
the slower ball and he pokes it down to point
86.2 mph, he cranks up the pace and the ball clips his pads and rolls away to the on side
moment of madness, he drops it short and wide and Akmal has a wild swish at it and misses it completely
this one nips back in and slices him in half, just beats the inside edge
bowls it fuller and Akmal shapes to crash that down the ground but he finds mid-off
shapes to drive straight but he gets an inside edge to the on side

excellent catch by Taylor, Butler drops it back of a length outside off and forces Malik to play at it, the ball dips and heads towards Taylor's left at first slip and he takes it inches off the ground
full and in the length to drive down the ground, he finds mid-off
hits a good length on middle and off, he gets behind the line and defends
gets across the stumps and defends down the track
drops it back of a length on middle and he swivels and pulls to deep square leg
a little slower in pace, Younis steers him softly to point
he oversteps this time, the batsman pushes it to point, slightly harsh call because part of his foot was touching the popping crease
Free Hit Franklin comes round the wicket and dishes out a friendly full toss, Younis bashes it high over mid-off's reach
comes back over the wicket this time and Younis clips it to midwicket
stands tall and fends it off to the off side

Kamran finds the fielder, he can't believe what he's done, he reaches out to a pitched up delivery outside off and scoops it high in the air down to Redmond at sweeper cover, he tumbles and takes it cleanly
Yousuf stays behind the line and defends to the off side
drops it back of a length and he shuffles and works it to midwicket
not much bounce there so Younis has to bend his knee slightly and chop it wide of cover point
lands it on middle and leg, he shuffles and works it to square leg
excellent running by Younis, Yousuf hops and dabs it down to gully and Younis charges away at the other end and comfortably beats the throw
shuffles and clips it to midwicket
hits a good length on the off stump and he defends to the off side
opens the face of the bat and squeezes it down to point
persists with that angle outside the off stump, pushed down to cover
angles it towards middle and leg, he turns the face of the bat and works it to the on side
holds the length back and he pulls it down to vacant spaces at square leg
drops it with soft hands and calls very quickly for the run, good judgement
gives him width outside off and he opens the face of the bat and angles it to third man
full outside off and defended to the off side
gets a half stride forward and defends with soft hands to the off side
hits a good length on the off stump and he pushes it to cover
tries to pierce that off side field again, Franklin keeps it nice and tight

chance for a run-out! Yousuf clips it towards short square leg and an alert and agile Guptill runs to his right, slides and in one motion has a shy at the batsman;s end, Yousuf turns around and almost gives up, he would've been out by miles
gets beside the line and pushes it to sweeper cover
lands outside off and angles away from the right-hander before reaching the keeper
pushes it firmly down the ground towards long-off
flighted outside off, he makes room and cuts with the turn
skids it through and he defends in front of his stumps
slower through the air and defended with a dead bat
lunges forward and chips it slightly towards short cover
slower through the air, no turn, he defends off the front foot
drops it fractionally short, waits for the turn and cuts to sweeper cover
fullish in length outside off, he pushes it down the pitch with soft hands
maintains that line outside of and Younis merely taps it with soft hands
he's happy keeping them away with soft hands
just turns the face of the bat and mistimes the drive to mid-off, the off side ring is packed
strays a bit on the pads and he clips it away down to the gap at square leg
flighted outside off and he makes room and cuts to point
pushes it a lot quicker and it turns and catches him on the back leg, half hearted appeal from McCullum
slower through the air, he waits for it and angles it to third man
gets forward and defends with a dead bat

very soft dismissal, flighted on the off stump,Younis commits to the front foot a little too early and he tries to work it to the on side, the ball spoons to Taylor at short cover off the leading edge
fires it in quick staightaway, defended back to the bowler
stays back and knocks it to the on side
angles it on middle and leg and he clips it with the line to square leg
grants him width outside off, he reaches out and effortlessly glides it wide of backward point and down to third man
stays beside the line and shapes to cut but he finds backward point, was in the air for a bit
comes round the wicket and lands it on a fullish length outside off, he pierces the gap and places it to sweeper cover
there was width to cut but he was too early on the shot, the ball rolls away towards the keeper
flighted outside off and defended on the front foot
he's content defending on the front foot again
slow through the air, lands it on a good length and Yousuf fails to pierce the gap at cover
down the leg side and he tickles it straight to short fine leg
flighted on middle and off and defended with a dead bat
Franklin keeps it tight, cramps him for room and Akmal stays back and defends with soft hands
tries to sneak it past midwicket but there's a fielder there to stop it
chance to crash a full delivery down the ground but he finds mid-off
this time he holds the length back and teases Akmal into gliding it down to third man, he's beaten on the shot
fullish in length outside off and he's content defending
gets beside the line and squeezes it past point
plays a pre-meditated paddle down to fine leg, he fetches it from outside off
lunges forward and defends with a dead bat
this one suddenly kicks up off a good length, he fends it off well by dropping his gloves
breaks the shackles, he gets on his knee early and seizes to slog it away, finds the big gap at deep midwicket
two in a row! Flighted outside off, he chops it hard to the off side but the ball balloons  off the top edge and beats short third man, Broom gives the chase
gets beside the line and steers it to the off side
lovely shot, half volley outside off, he leans forward and caresses it past the gap between mid-off and cover
gets behind the line and defends
gets width outside off and he tries to angle it down to third man but it's that man Ross Taylor who flings himself to his right and stops it
drops it fractionally short and he swivels and pulls to deep square leg
gets forward and nearly spoons it on the full to cover

chance of a run-out, the ball was on the pads, tipped to the leg side, Yousuf charges down for a single, sent back, McCullum rushes out and fields and shies at the stumps, Yousuf was back just in time
defended to midwicket by Yousuf
played with soft hands towards the off side
punched off the backfoot towards cover
quicker one, defended off the back foot
and that's a maiden, Vettori sends the ball on a length just outside off, Yousuf gets well forward and defends
Akmal goes for a big drive off the first ball, mistimes it back towards the bowler, it was a length ball well outside off
slightly shorter and closer to the stumps this time, opens the face and guides it past slip
Mills keeps it tight, just outside off, Yousuf defends off the front foot
back of a length, in the channel outside off, Yousuf pushes it off the front foot towards cover
a touch shorter this time, Yousuf steers it behind backward point for a single
ends with a quick short ball just outside off, Akmal sways out of the way and keeps his bat low as he lets that one go
fired in towards middle stump, Yousuf turns it towards midwicket
length ball outside off, Akmal gets on the front foot and tickles it behind square leg
another single, this time to cover point, three in a row this over
played with soft hands towards square leg for another single, nicely done by Akmal
slightly overpitched on middle and leg, Yousuf punches it towards short midwicket
Yousuf clips the ball behind square leg to pick off another easy single, no risks but five runs in the over for Pakistan
short of length, Yousuf shuffles across and pulls it towards deep midwicket
short and wide outside off, Akmal pulls it over mid-on, not too well timed but enough on it to clear the infield
another short ball from Mills, this time on a middle stump line, Akmal sways out of the way
again Mills tests Akmal with a bouncer, Akmal gets on his toes and dabs the ball towards third man
Mills reverts to a good length, line is just  outside off, Yousuf cautiously defends off the front foot
on middle stump this time, Yousuf looks to work it towards square leg, inside-edges it onto his pads
cracking shot from Akmal, a touch short from Vettori, not too wide outside off, Akmal backs away to make room and crunches it off the backfoot past cover point
and another one, again not much room, that doesn't stop Akmal from clobbering it past a diving cover point for four
on the pads, clipped towards square leg
Yousuf helps himself to a single by pushing the ball towards mid-on
just outside off, Akmal mistimes it past the keeper
Akmal looks to tip the ball to the leg side and get a single, but doesn't time the ball and it drops at his feet
Butler starts with a back of length ball just outside off, Yousuf opens the face to glide the ball towards gully, where Ross Taylor dives and fields
gets forward and pushes the ball towards cover point
tucked off the pads towards midwicket for a single
full and wide outside off, Akmal looked to jab that behind point, misses the ball
back of a length, just outside off, Akmal tries to dab that to third man, again he doesn't make contact, he's annoyed with himself
this time he runs a fullish ball to third man for a single
slightly overpitched outside off, punched towards the bowler
played with soft hands towards cover, the batsmen zip through for a single
Yousuf stands tall and pushes the ball off his pads towards mid-on
big appeal from McCullum after Akmal misses the ball once more while attempting to run it to third man
defended to the leg side, Yousuf wants a run, sent back by Akmal
this time they get the single, Akmal sweeps the ball behind square leg, not too well timed, the ball just dribbles behind square
Akmal has decided that third man is his favourite region, once more he looks to guide a ball close to offstump there, but is beaten
short ball outside off, Akmal lets it through to the keeper, was nearly high enough to be a wide
more signs of impatience from Akmal, a length ball well outside off and Akmal looks to hammer that through the covers, no contact again
neatly dabbed to third man for a single this time, stood on his toes and opened the face
Yousuf stays on the backfoot and carves the ball behind backward point, where Grant Elliott dives despairingly to his left
short ball, Akmal ducks awkwardly, the ball was andling down leg and that's a wide
another swish outside off, he doesn't seem to tire of trying that one, again his attempt to glide the ball to third man ends with him missing it
short of length, just outside off, Yousuf gets forward and taps the ball towards the bowler
steered down to third man this time for a single
a back of the hand slower ball from Elliott, loops towards Akmal, ends up as a near yorker on middle stump, blocked back to the bowler
shortish and outside off, Akmal guides the ball to third man for a single
Shane Bond at third man is getting a real workout this over, again the ball is glided to him for a single
guess what? another single to third man, that's what, this ball was on off and middle, Akmal skips back to make room and then pokes the ball to third man
swing and a miss outside off, shortish ball which the batsman wanted to hammer over point
Akmal tries to nibble the ball to third man, once more he misses, that was a back of a length and just outside off
slower ball, 122.6kmh, Akmal gets the ball towards third man this time, he opens the face and gets it just wide of the keeper
length ball on the pads, Akmal shuffles across and helps the ball to fine leg
short ball on middle, Yousuf swivels as he pulls that one down to fine leg
back of a length, heading for offstump, defended off the backfoot towards point
length ball on off, Yousuf taps it off the front foot back towards the bowler
on the pads, flicked in the air towards square leg, lands safely
on middle and leg again, Yousuf again whips it behind square leg
short of length, chopped towards point, the ball dribbles towards the fielder, Broom, who fumbles, and a single is taken, 150 comes up
full ball outside off, driven crisply but straight to the cover fielder
on the pads this time, tucked away towards midwicket for an easy single
length ball outside off, driven elegantly towards sweeper cover for a single
short ball on off, cramping Akmal for room, jumps and defends that towards cover point
short and wide, slower one, 125kmh, Yousuf cleverly dinks that between the keeper and fly slip for four
fullish ball on legstump, defends the ball towards the bowler
ovepitched on offstump, driven to the bowler's right for a single
Akmal calls for two immediately after tucking that short of length ball behind square leg, played with soft hands and the batsmen sprint through the second
just outside off, Yousuf blocks the ball back down the pitch
angling into middle, Yousuf shuffles across and turns the ball towards midwicket
nips in after pitching a short of a length, Akmal rocks back and cuts it towards backward point
lovely shot from Yousuf, slightly full delivery on middle, caressed  past mid-on for four, fantastic timing on that one
great response from the bowler, a length ball outside off, nips back in and sneaks between bat and pad, the ball sails over the stumps
played on, Yousuf is bowled, it was a back of length just outside off, Yousuf wanted to run it to third man as he has so often this innings, gets an inside edge onto off stump
Frankling bowls a slow ball on middle and leg, defended back to the bowler
angling across the batsman, who opens the face and tickles the ball towards third man
shot! slightly overpitched outside off, a cracking drive past short cover from Akmal
jabbed towards backward point, 'No' is the call from Akmal as soon as he plays the shot
Akmal brings up his half-century by guiding the ball off his pads towards long leg
tips the ball towards the off side, takes a couple of steps looking for the single, sent back by Afridi
arm ball, sliding onto legstump, turned towards midwicket for a single
'Two' Akmal screams as he tucks the ball towards midwicket, but the fielder was onto the ball quickly so the batsmen settle for one
full, on middle and leg, clipped to square leg
Akmal sashays down the track and hammers that one over cover for four, great shot that

Akmal is gone, lbw, he was looking to paddle that one fine, he misses and is struck on the pads, Taufel sends him on his way, the ball looked to be heading for offstump, but Akmal was extremely unhappy with the decision, was there an inside edge? Replays show there was, a thick one too
full ball, slanting down leg, the batsman is hit on the pads
Afridi goes for a flamboyant pull, not middled but it lands wide of the fielder at midwicket

another batsmen goes attempting to run the ball to third man, it was a bit wide outside off, Afridi nibbles it through to the keeper, massive blow for Pakistan, will Younis be regretting not having taken the Powerplay when Yousuf and Akmal were set?
Gul is greeted with a bouncer, just outside off, Gul ducks under it, it's too high for the umpire's liking, didn't look that high though
inside-edged onto the thigh pad this time
fullish ball, Gul looks to drive, inside-edge take the ball towards fine leg
full and outside off, a good-looking cover drive from Naved, a bit of hesitation but the batsmen get two
nearly played on there, a back of length delivery outside off, inside-edge towards the stumps but the ball bounces over
fullish ball, blocked off the front foot
pushed off the backfoot towards cover
Gul stands tall and punches the ball towards sweeper cover
pushed towards cover, straight at the fielder
jabbed off the backfoot towards cover this time, again at the fielder
slightly overpitched, heading for offstump, defended back towards the bowler
outside off, Gul swishes at that one and misses
another swing at an outside off ball, thick outside edge takes the ball just over Ross Taylor at slip, the ball races away to the boundary
another footwork-free swing from Gul, mishit, the ball balloons to cover point, Broom moves to his right to take the skier
full ball on middle and off, blocked back to the bowler by Aamer
backs away and chops the ball towards backward point
Butler keeps it tidy, short of length, on offstump, defended off the backfoot
hello Powerplays, first ball is absolutely clobbered over extra cover, Naved was charged out of the crease before unleashing a powerful swipe

he's gone this time, attempts to clear the boundary once more, gets a top egde which swirls to Guptill at midwicket, Guptill has to make some ground to take that catch, completing it outside the circle
Aamer looks to cut that wide delivery but is beaten
gets forward and defends the ball towards the off side
played with soft hands towards cover point
and again the batsman defends watchfully back down the pitch
angling down the leg side, hits the pads and dribble toward short fine leg
switches his line towards offstump, tipped towards the off side
short of length on the pads, tucked behind square leg, the batsmen take a quick single, the batsman was struggling to make his ground but the throw was poor to the keeper's end
nudged towards cover point off the backfoot
gets on the front foot, and pushes the ball towards cover
straying down the leg side, strikes the batsman's pads, the ball rolls down the pitch
played towards square leg, another dot ball
superb shot from Aamer, stands tall and carves a short ball past cover point, Bond offered plenty of room for the batsman there
no room need this time, Aamer backs away and lashes a full ball on legstump past cover four
poor delivery that, well down the leg side, all valuable runs for Pakistan
full and just outside off, Aamer looks to crash that past short cover but mistimes the shot
another boundary for Aamer and Pakistan, a short ball is pulled, not too well timed but enough on it to take it for four over midwicket
played with soft hands towards point, no run this time
again tips it to cover point, charges down for a single this time, sent back wisely by Aamer
slashes at a ball well outside off, gets an edge to third man which brings Aamer on strike
a bouncer down the leg stump, Aamer has backed away too far down leg, so the ball passes between the batsman and the stumps
another superbly timed drive from Aamer, length ball just outside off, Aamer backs away a touch and throws his bat at the ball
on legstump, Aamer gets on the backfoot and defends the ball towards the leg side

speared into middle and leg, Ajmal punches the ball towards mid-on and sets off for a suicidal single, Aamer was really late to react, a direct hit at either end would have caught the batsmen short but Redmond misses at the non-striker's end
short ball, Aamer slashes it in the air towards deep backward square leg
a ripper of a delivery from Bond, Ajmal is beaten outside off

this time Ajmal gets Pakistan four runs, clipped the ball toward square leg, Butler races across at the boundary to cut that, he dives and stops the ball but his body is in contact with the ropes as he fielded, the crowd roars as the umpire signals four after several replays
cut behind point for more runs, the Pakistan fans in the ground are loving this
length ball slanting into the pads, pushed towards mid-on for a single
short and wide outside off, ooh, nearly a wide that one
Ajaml goes for a wild heave, misses the ball which was on a length just outside off
slower ball, Ajmal looks to swing it over cover, misses the ball outside off
What a shot that is, a length delivery outside off, Ajmal paddles it  very fine down the leg side for four
full delivery outside off, driven firmly towards mid-off
a yorker just outside off, jammed towards the off side, Pakistan end on 233

inn2.comm: starts off with a good length ball on middle and leg, he shuffles and knocks it down to short midwicket
into the crowd! Aamer drops it short and hits the deck really hard, McCullum plays a savage pull and the ball is skied for quite a while but lands over the deep midwicket rope
short and slightly wide, he pushes it down to point
86.9 mph, bowls it on a fullish length outside off and the ball moves back in off the seam
angles it across the right-hander and he safely lets it go
87.1 mph, cranks up the pace, lands it just wide of the off stump on a fullish length and McCullum leaves it alone
drops it short of a length on middle and leg, he shuffles and tucks it behind square on the on side, hurries through for the second run
just short of a length and the ball stops on him a bit, he manages to defend with soft hands
lands it on middle and off and McCullum defends solidly
quite stylish! Rana drops it short of a length directed down the leg side and the batsman swivels on one leg, rolls his wrists and pulls, picks the gap at fine leg
digs it in short outside off, he gets his elbows high and upper cuts it down to third man

he's making it look very easy here, not a bad delivery, good length on middle and leg but Redmond knows where the fielders are on the on side and he picks the big gap at square leg to whip it away with little effort
gets cheeky by getting on his knees early, paddles it around to long leg
stays right behind the line and defends
87.3 mph, pacy delivery which leaves the right hander, well left
gets across to follow the angle and he pushes it to the off side
maintains that line outside the off stump and the batsman is happy to let it go
good bounce and carry to the keeper again, just a hint of late inward movement

doesn't pick the slower ball well and he plays a checked drive spooned towards mid-off, they go through with the single and the fielder has a shy at the batsman's end, a direct hit would have been interesting
stays beside the line and he taps it to point
stays back and punches it firmly off the meat of the bat
another slower ball but he jams it down to mid-off
stays back and punches him down towards extra cover, Afridi effects a sliding save but it doesn't prevent a single
shuffles across early to state his intentions but Rana keeps it straight and the batsman has to settle for a defensive shot
fires it full outside off and a firm drive finds backward point

Afridi pouches a skier, he's flat on his back with his arms outstretched! McCullum is tempted into chasing a delivery full and wide of the off stump, he tries to take him downtown over deep extra cover but he miscues it and Afridi pedals backwards from the circle, takes the catch and tumbles backwards
another lifter from Aamer, keeps the right hander guessing
now Redmond is teased into chasing something wide of the off stump, not too far from the edge there
stays behind  the line and defends
stays back and punches it in front of mid-on and sets off quickly
gets right behind the line and defends solidly down the track
terrific shot, Rana pitches it up outside off, Redmond follows the swing, lofts through the line and nearly sends the ball over the wide long-off rope
on the pads and he just gets a light trickle down to fine leg
hits a good length on the off stump and he stays behind the line and punches it to short cover
bowls the slower ball and lands it close to the yorker length, dug out back to the bowler
rolls his fingers and bowls the off cutter, just gets it to leave the right-hander
lands it outside off and he watchfully lets it go
loses his radar and sprays it wide outside the off stump, the batsman isn't going to chase that
wide of the off stump again, left alone by Redmond
same ball same result, left alone
cranks up the pace and Aamer continues to get encouraging bounce and carry to the keeper
this is a very restrictive line, bowls that at 87 mph and gets good carry to Akmal
hits a good length on middle and leg, he punches it to cover
that's Guptill's signature shot! Drops it fractionally short and Guptill lifts one leg and plays a short arm pull with little effort, gets the height and elevation to clear deep midwicket
fuller in length and squeezed out to mid-on
hits a good length on the off stump and he defends back to the bowler
just as good as the six, Rana bowls the slower ball wide of the off stump, Guptill gets on one knee and plays an elegant square drive, gets the placement right and beats backward point
holds the length back outside off and he taps it to point
and meanwhile Aamer continues to keep Redmond quiet, not as much bounce this time and Redmond shapes to play a flashy cut but misses
not anymore, this time Aamer drops it a bit too short and cuts back on the pace, that gives Redmond the chance to punch him in the air very firmly past point and cover
beats him with a slower ball, well bowled
appeal! Pitches outside leg and traps him on the pads, wait there was a thick inside edge
punches it to cover
stays beside the line and punches it to the off side

that's a very soft dismissal and aren't Pakistan glad! Guptill perishes to the same short-arm pull which fetched him a six, wasn't short enough to play that shot and he was cramped as well, the top edge lands down Rana's throat at mid-on
stays behind the line and defends solidly down the pitch
stays beside the line and taps it firmly to the off side
stays beside the line and pushes him down to point
gets right across his stumps and Gul cramps him up, he defends back to the bowler
pushes it to the off side and tells his partner to stay back
lands it outside off and he follows the line and angles it down to third man
gets back and across and steers it to the off side
that's a good shot, Aamer bowls it fuller and gives Taylor just the right amount of width to bend forward and smack that past cover point
stays back and defends off the meat of the bat
nervy moment for Taylor as he gets forward, fails to read the off cutter properly and nearly spoons it to short cover, well bowled there
Gul hits the deck hard and the bouncer shoots over Redmond's arched back, the umpire signals one for the over
raw power, short and wide outside off, it sat up waiting to be hit, he slapped it over backward point and the ball nearly carried over the rope
good length outside off, left alone
nice bouncer this time, hits the deck hard outside off and it fizzes past his body
hits a good length on the off stump, he gets back and defends
Aamer tirelessly runs in, hits the deck hard outside off and he bends backward and lets it go
stays back and defends with soft hands
keeps it nice and tight on the off stump, gets behind the line and defends
bowls the same teasing line outside the off stump and Taylor is happy to let it go
angles it across the right-hander and Taylor gets his backlift high and lets it go

an over dramatised appeal there! But entertaining all the same and Aamer smiles, it landed outside leg, skidded through and trapped him on the pads, Aamer slips and he's on all fours during the appeal
stays beside the line and taps it towards point and there's a misfield
tip and run, he drops his wrists and snatches a quick single to the off side
gets behind the line and defends to the on side
an attempted yorker turns into a low full toss down the leg side, the batsman just helps it along it's way and finds the gap at long leg
just hops at the crease and angles it wide of backward point
lands it on a good length outside off, he chops it to the off side
flighted outside off, he gets forward and pushes it to cover
flighted outside off, he makes room and thuds it straight to mid-off
quicker through the air and skids it through, defended to the off side
cries of 'catch it'! Redmond tries to smack it over backward point but he miscues it and the ball drops in front of Nazir at the deep, perhaps he should have gone for it
drops it in front of cover and completes a sharp single
flighted outside off and defended to the off side
hits a good length outside off, he taps it hard down to point
stays beside the line and punches it just wide of cover point
drops his wrists and pinches a quick single to point, beats the throw at the bowler's end
drops the ball down in front of point again but doesn't take a single this time
excellent running again, he knocks it wide of the bowler towards mid-on and puts pressure on the fielder
he sways out of a slow bouncer but Akmal lets that slip through his legs on the bounce, Malik gives the charge and does well to pull it back
tip and run again,drops it towards cover and completes the single easily, they're happy with this strategy
quicker through the air, gets forward and knocks it in front of point and sets off
pushes it firmly down the track back to the bowler

listen to the crowd roar! Looked like the doosra which Redmond failed to pick, slow through the air, Redmond is early on the shot as he walks towards the pitch of the ball and he ends up spooning it back to Ajmal, the easiest of catches
very close to wicket No.4! The offcutter traps him on the forward prod, looked very close and all the Pakistanis went up, Ian Gould shook his head
gets off the mark with a single to point
drops it fractionally short and he meets the ball high on the bat and defends
it's an overstep! Ten marks out of ten for placement there, he seizes on a short delivery, nonchalantly swings his arms and bisects a small enough gap at deep square leg
Free Hit: 140.8 kph, wastes the opportunity there, backs away early and Gul fires a yorker outside off, he fails to get bat on ball
appeal for a run out, he pinches a single to cover and there's a direct hit by Umar Akmal, he dives and makes it home, the third umpire has a look
they're hitting the stumps again but he's safe, taps it to cover point and sets off quickly, the direct hit was a couple of seconds late
Gul puts in that extra bit of effort and gets the ball to kick up and fizz past Elliott, well bowled
flat down the leg side and he gets a faint trickle down to short fine leg, I have no idea what Kamran was appealing for
sharp turn, watch out guys! lands outside off and hits him on the pads outside the line of leg, confident appeal and Gould shakes his head
quicker through the air and worked away to the on side
flighted on middle and leg, he works it with the  turn to deep midwicket
takes the risk of cutting him against the turn with the ball skidding through and honing in on the stumps
tucks it with the turn down to short fine leg
risky! Reaches out to cut but gets an under edge past the keeper
flighted outside off and he reaches out and places it to point
clips it against the turn to square leg
gets to the pitch of the ball and works him to midwicket
flighted outside off and defended to the off side
flighted on middle and leg,  pushed with the turn to mid-on
gets forward and angles it down to point
quicker and flatter, he taps it down to short square leg
shuffles and clips it past square leg
punches it straight and firm to midwicket
floated down the leg side and he gets a leading edge which rolls back to Ajmal
grips off the surface and the turn squares him up, beaten all ends up
gets forward and knocks it to square leg
same ball same shot, midwicket picks it up
gives him width outside off and he drives to point
quicker through the air and he defends it down to the off side
drops it fractionally short and he rocks back and cuts to sweeper cover
gets on his knee and tries to swipe him across the line, the impact was outside the line of the off stump
gives him width outside the off stump and he drives to the off side
floated down the leg side and wide called
stays back and punches him through the line to long-on
flighted on middle and leg, he turns his wrists and knocks it to midwicket
tucked to the on side
stays back and chops it to the off side
drops it a bit short and he pulls to the deep at midwicket
fires it on the blockhole and Elliott nearly lets it roll onto his stumps
gets forward and chops it to point
pushed through quicker, he digs it out of the blockhole
chips down the track and pushes it through the line to long-off
slow through the air and defended with soft hands
gets forward and defends to the on side
that will come as a huge sigh of relief for NZ, he gets on his knee and slog sweeps him high over deep midwicket
slow through the air and defended with a dead bat
picks the doosra and defends with a dead bat
shortish ball on off, skips away and carves it to backward point
struck firmly to Younis Khan at short cover
again Younis Khan has work to do, the batsman pushes it off the front foot
three in a row, as Taylor again punches the ball towards short cover
rocks back and plays it towards backward point
played with soft hands square on the off side
back of a length ball heading for off, blocked back to the bowler
another dot ball, again cautious forward defensive from Taylor
angling into the pads, tucked towards midwicket for a single
a firm pull from Elliott, Nazir slides to stop the ball at deep square leg, a bit of a fumble but only a single taken
better running this time, punched to long-on, where Mohammad Yousuf is fielding, the batsmen zip back for the second
Taylor gets well forward and eases the ball towards long-off
pushed off the front foot towards extra cover for a single
rocks back and punches the ball towards extra cover
fullish ball, a bump ball to Younis Khan at short cover, the crowd gets excited
played uppishly towards cover point, lands just short of the fielder
pushed quicker down the leg side
on middle and leg this time, nudged to the leg side
back of a length, tight offstump line, Taylor blocks it back to the bowler
an inswinging yorker, big appeal for lbw, looks to have inside-edged it onto the pads
the balls definitely started to swing here, the ball cannons towards the leg side, struck on the pads but the ball was heading down leg
keeps it full, this time well outside off, guided down to third man
length ball on middle, Elliott shows the full face of the bat as he defends it back down the pitch
full and outside off, pushed towards short cover
full ball, just outside off, carved past cover for two
played with soft hands towards short cover
Afridi is convinced that is lbw, a massive appeal from him, but that was easily missing leg
a monster hit from Taylor, shortish ball, quickly onto the backfoot and clobbered over midwicket and out of the ground
Afridi has done the trick, the new ball works, Taylor is bowled, he was looking to cut that delivery, thinking it would turn, but it went straight on and hits the stumps, big wicket for Pakistan
greeted with a full toss on off and middle, pushed back to the bowler
on legstump, clipped towards midwicket for a single
on the pads, tucks it towards square leg for a single
sensible batting from New Zealand, third single in a row after easing the ball to long-on
no-ball, angling across Vettori, who shoulders arms, free-hit time
great ball, a yorker well outside off, jabbed towards deep backward point for a single
length ball just outside off, dabbed towards backward point
played with soft hands towards mid-on, it was a tight single but the batsmen take on the fielder, who misses the stumps
Elliott skips away from stumps, Afridi follows him, blocked towards short cover
neatly paddle-swept by Elliott for two, does this guy ever put any power behind his shots?
carved towards backward point, straight at the fielder
slashed in front of point for a single
Vettori gets well forward and punches the ball towards long-off
angling into legstump, Elliott drops it at his feet and looks for the single but is sent back
Vettori works the first ball off his pads towards square leg for a single
Elliott is drawn towards an outside-off delivery, he looks to defend but is beaten
length ball just outside off, defended back to the bowler
Gul keeps it tight outside off, Elliottt chops this one to backward point
Gul keeps pegging away at offstump, four dot balls in a row as Elliott can only poke this one towards point
make that five in a row, only one from the over, Elliott crunches that one but Malik at backward point cuts it off
dropped towards point for a quick single
short and wide, Elliott was backing away and the ball was too wide outside off for Elliott to reach
full ball just outside off, cracked to sweeper cover for a couple
nearly a catch, Elliott slashes it to backward point, where Malik dives full length to his right to stop the ball which lands inches ahead of him
Vettori nudges the ball towards square leg
short ball, cut towards backward point, straight to Shoaib Malik
again Malik has to do the fielding as Vettori pushes the ball to backward point
slightly wide outside off, cut away in front of point for an easy single
'Wait in' says Elliott after slashing the ball to backward point again
short and wide, Elliott goes for the cut but bottom-edges it onto the pitch
full ball on middle and leg, tucked away to deep midwicket for a couple
looking for the yorker, ends up a touch shorter, on offstump, punched to long-on for a single
one of the biggest appeals for lbw I have seen, the batsman is hit high on the pads, Hawk-Eye says it's just about clipping top of the leg bail, umpire Taufel disagrees
punched to long-off for a single
gets forward and drives through cover for a single

another massive appeal, pitched well outside leg though, there was a chance of a run-out at the non-striker's end as the batsmen went for the single, the throw misses with the batsman well out, Afridi doesn't attempt to collect it at the stumps either
the ball dribbles to the leg side after an inside-edge onto the pads
gets forward and defends to the off side
driven towards cover for a single by Vettori, who has not attempted a single big shot till now
way down the leg side
Elliott is struck on the pads after he takes a big stride forward, was going over the top of the stumps
turned away to fine leg for a single
big spin for Malik, Vettori goes for the sweep but is beaten by the turn
fuller ball this time, Vettori sweeps again, top-edge swirls towards fine leg, lands short of fine leg
turned towards midwicket, straight at the fielder
93kmh, on the pads, clipped to square leg
lovely drive from Elliott, length ball that is lofted over extra cover by Elliott
pushed towards short cover off the front foot
punched down to long-off for an easy single
on the pads, tucked behind square leg for another comfortable single
92.2kmh, a yorker on off, squeezed out towards point
watchfully defended off the front foot
just outside off, Elliott shuffles across but mistimes his attempted flick
this time the flick comes off, he gets a single to midwicket
Vettori defends off the front foot towards point
on legstump, worked behind square leg for another single
fullish outside off, Elliott sweeps that to square leg
outside off, jabbed to backward point

dropped< what has Younis done? the simplest catch you will ever see, Elliott chips the ball to short cover, lobs gently to Younis, who gets on his knees and tries to take it the Aussie way, I can't recollect a simpler catch going down
outside off, left alone for the keeper
punched to deep extra cover for a single this time
length ball just outside off, nudged towards point

another mix-up, Elliott pushes the ball to mid-on and sets off for the single, Vettori hesitates and both batsmen are stuck mid-pitch before they decide to go for the run, the throw misses at the keeper's end
defended towards short cover
a strident appeal for lbw, struck outside the line
length ball slanting into leg stump, driven towards mid-on
full ball on the pads, driven to midwicket, Younis does the fielding, cleanly this time
full, on middle and leg, driven to mid-on for a single
Vettori rocks onto the backfoot and tucks the ball behind square leg, as he has so many times already today
blocked back towards the bowler this time, another dot ball, difference between balls and runs is 11
bouncer, over the batsman's head, and Aamer will have to re-bowl that
full on offstump,  driven back to the bowler
another big appeal, Pakistan are bemused after the appeal is turned down, the yorker struck Vettori marginally outside off, great call from Taufel
defended towards short cover with soft hands
a length ball outside off, a cross-batted swat is mistimed towards midwicket
another single for Elliott, turned towards mid-on this time
on middle, turned towards deep square leg for a single
Vettori gets his front foot out of the way and swipes the ball towards deep midwicket, there's a chase for Malik who cuts  it off
a flat-batted swat from Vettori, along the ground to mid-on for a single
short ball, on offstump, Elliott punches it towards extra cover
four, slightly overpitched ball on the pads, Vettori gets the front foot out of the way and swings it wide of mid-on for four
yorker on legstump, jabbed towards mid-on for a single
full and outside off, Vettori walks well across the stumps and nurdles it to the leg side
fifty to Elliott, gets the landmark with a typical push towards cover
Elliott may like the singles but Vettori is hitting top gear here, a fullish ball is clubbed back past the bowler for four
and again Vettori walks across the stumps and tries to swing the ball past short fine leg, any bat on it and that would have been four, luckily for Pakistan Vettori misses
superb delivery from Aamer, what temperament from a 17-year-old? full and outside off, Vettori is beaten
Vettori skips away to make room, and slashes that towards cover for a single
disastrous start to the over for Naved, a length ball on middle and leg, swiped to midwicket for four, free-hit coming up, that was a big no-ball as well
the free-hit is lashed to long-on for a single
the famous Naved slower ball, 104kmh,  back of the hand delivery, Elliott goes for the cut and is beaten
another no-ball, these are freebies for New Zealand, another big no-ball, this is poor stuff from Naved, Elliott punches it wide of long-on, free-hit to come
way outside off, Elliott carves it to backward point for a single, that was another slower ball
yet another slower ball, 102kmh, perhaps the quicker ball is his surprise delivery? this one is lashed through covers for two more
one more slow delivery, dabbed towards point by Vettori
finishes off with - you guessed it - a slower ball, Elliott makes room to cut, and dabs it towards the off side
fantastic shot from Elliott, full ball on off, backs away and lofts that between cover and extra cover for four, first ball for a boundary takes the pressure off
Elliott shows us he's not a single-specialist, another boundary, again full, this time Elliott launches it wide of mid-on

whoah, Elliott is turning on the style, singles? what are they, he says, smacks that one over midwicket for six, New Zealand are nearly home, it will need an almighty choke from here for New Zealand to go out
reverts to the let-me-just-drop-it-and take-a-single mode, dabbing it to backward point
Vettori clips the ball to deep square leg for another single
plays it with soft hands, but the ball drops dead at his feet, no run
Vettori sweeps from well outside off towards square leg
Elliott is finishing this in a hurry, comes down the track, and opens the face as he drives the ball past cover, picked the doosra early there
off the pads, the ball runs towards point for one
Vettori is down the track and turns the ball to midwicket for a single
Elliott swings the ball down to fine leg for a single
Vettori is gone, too little too late for Pakistan, Vettori goes down the pitch and goes for a big heave, misses the ball, Akmal has an easy stumping
Elliott glides the ball to third man for a single, moving on to 75
the scores are level as Broom steers the ball wide of third man for a couple
full and just outside, punched to extra cover
big appeal for lbw, full ball looked to be sliding down leg, there was an inside-edge as well
fantastic yorker from Gul, but it's in vain as Broom digs it out and the batsmen zip through for a single, New Zealand are through, Pakistan are out
